      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>How do all the hip and fashionable people who find cocaine so glamorous justify the means by which cocaine comes into their possession?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>How do all the hip and fashionable people who find cocaine so glamorous justify the means by which cocaine comes into their possession?</p>
        <p>Most of these people would likely assert that it's a terrible thing to buy garments made in sweatshops or by child laborers. But buying illegal drugs that enrich lowlife dealers, encouraging people to risk their lives acting as mules, wrecking local economies in other countries and having many other detrimental effects on people's lives and livelihoods  they're O.K. with all that?</p>
        <p>Kathleen Gray  Scarsdale, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
